==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[Abecedary]]

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[abecedarius]]''. A word formed from the first four letters of the Latin alphabet.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One who is learning the alphabet; hence, a [[tyro]].
# One engaged in [[teaching]] the alphabet
# One who is a beginner in some field.
# {{rhetoric}} A series of terms in an utterance in alphabetical order.
{{examples-right|examples=He knew his rhetorical devices from abecedarian, battologia, and contentio, all the way to zeugma}}

